               <ce:simple-para id="biospara0010" view="all">
                  <ce:bold>Fabio Aricò:</ce:bold> Fabio Aricò obtained his master's degree in chemistry from the University of Messina. He was awarded a Ph.D. at Reading University (UK) and then spent 2 years as postdoctoral fellow in Stoddart group at the UCLA (USA). In 2005, he moved back to Italy at the University Ca’ Foscari where he is associate Professor since 2015. He published more than 60 articles; main research interests are Green Chemistry, Chlorine-free chemistry, dialkyl carbonates and biobased platform chemicals.</ce:simple-para>
            </ce:biography>
            <ce:biography id="vt2" view="all">
               <ce:simple-para id="biospara0015" view="all">
                  <ce:bold>Ramón Moreno Tost:</ce:bold> Ramón Moreno Tost is a professor at the Inorganic, Crystallography and Mineralogy Department, University of Málaga, Spain. He received his degree in chemistry (1994) and Ph.D. (2002) from the University of Málaga. His research interest is focused on the catalysts synthesis with different functionalities applied to the conversion of biomass to fuels and bioproducts. He is authored of more than 70 articles in high impact factor journal, 3 book chapters and 2 patents with an h-index of 27.</ce:simple-para>
